And we take the blood and we apply the blood of Jesus over every single one of us tonight.

00:56:17.333 --> 00:56:25.149
We apply the blood of Jesus and we make much of the blood and the blood makes much of us.

00:56:25.149 --> 00:56:31.013
We apply the blood all around our houses.

00:56:31.013 --> 00:56:35.696
We apply the blood over our families.

00:56:35.696 --> 00:56:40.640
We apply the blood over our children.

00:56:40.640 --> 00:56:51.699
We apply the blood over our workplace where we go to work, over our churches that there'll be a great revival starting with us.

00:56:51.699 --> 00:57:06.331
And we take the blood of Jesus right now in the name of Jesus, and we give you all the glory.

00:57:06.331 --> 00:57:08.479
Amen and amen.

00:57:08.479 --> 00:57:10.079
Thank you, Lord.

00:57:10.079 --> 00:57:15.211
We give all of the glory to Jesus and tell of his love, his wonderful love.

00:57:15.211 --> 00:57:29.750
We give all of the glory to Jesus and tell of his wonderful love.

00:57:29.760 --> 00:57:31.360
Do you believe that?

00:57:31.360 --> 00:57:31.960
It's time.

00:57:32.560 --> 00:57:41.119
I'll tell you more about what I saw about Jesus if you want to know more about that visitation, and I can go into more detail about it.

00:57:43.120 --> 00:57:55.680
I realize there's so many new faces that are coming here all the time that don't hear all the visitations that I've had—the angelic visitations pushing us in the truck when we ran out of gas on the side of the road.

00:57:55.680 --> 00:57:58.292
Fifty percent haven't heard of the angel pushing a truck down.

00:57:58.292 --> 00:57:58.933
How high?

00:57:58.933 --> 00:57:59.787
Wow, 52% now.

00:57:59.787 --> 00:58:04.608
Fifty-two percent never heard that.

00:58:04.608 --> 00:58:05.072
Fifty-three.

00:58:05.072 --> 00:58:07.006
I'll just tell it now.

00:58:07.006 --> 00:58:11.386
There's too many of y'all who hadn't heard that.

00:58:11.386 --> 00:58:12.549
Fifty-five now.

00:58:12.549 --> 00:58:13.240
No joke.

00:58:13.240 --> 00:58:14.880
Okay, well, we'll hear about it.

00:58:14.880 --> 00:58:16.069
You want to listen?

00:58:16.069 --> 00:58:16.529
Okay.

00:58:20.662 --> 00:58:20.960
It was about...

00:58:29.031 --> 00:58:29.342
I was driving down Covell and I-35.

00:58:37.669 --> 00:58:41.096
I just passed Covell on I-35, like I was talking last time, and I was headed towards Guthrie, Oklahoma, and it was right before you got to Waterloo.

00:58:47.636 --> 00:58:47.813
It was in between Covell and Waterloo, and I was driving down the road.

00:58:49.200 --> 00:58:53.680
It was about 97 degrees outside, and it was hot, hot, hot.

00:58:53.680 --> 00:59:02.457
And my wife was pregnant with our third child, and she was big and pregnant.

00:59:02.457 --> 00:59:04.600
This is whenever you're getting miserable.

00:59:07.119 --> 00:59:17.778
And we were going down the road and my old truck, the gas gauge was broken on it, so you never knew when it was full or empty.

00:59:22.533 --> 00:59:28.559
And I was coming back from the church, and I had just finished cleaning and polishing the floors, and it was hot.

00:59:28.559 --> 00:59:32.849
There was no air conditioner in this thing.

00:59:34.359 --> 00:59:41.839
I had the windows down and all of a sudden, the truck shut off.

00:59:41.839 --> 00:59:52.569
I pulled over to the side of the road, and it wouldn't start.

00:59:56.839 --> 00:59:57.119
It was completely dead.

00:59:58.047 --> 01:00:04.016
It ran out of gas, and I was like, 'Oh Lord,' because my pregnant wife's in the car.

01:00:04.016 --> 01:00:05.316
I got my other two.

01:00:05.316 --> 01:00:09.800
Megan's really at this time really overcoming bad autism stuff, and Braden's little.

01:00:09.800 --> 01:00:24.960
So they were just little, and I was just praying in the Spirit, grabbed the wheel of my truck, and I just started praying, 'Oh, God, send me...

01:00:24.960 --> 01:00:26.194
I need help.

01:00:26.194 --> 01:00:33.520
I can't leave my family in this truck and walk down the road.

01:00:33.520 --> 01:00:34.799
' And it was hot.

01:00:34.799 --> 01:00:39.333
So, all of a sudden, I feel this...

01:00:39.333 --> 01:00:53.146
I'm pulled over, and I feel this bam, and everybody's head yanked forward.

01:01:06.400 --> 01:01:06.893
I thought we had been rear-ended, that's how hard we were yanked.

01:01:13.280 --> 01:01:18.140
And all of a sudden, I see this angel with these massive wings spread out like Angels in the Outfield.

01:01:24.223 --> 01:01:24.847
I'm talking like massive wings.

01:01:40.960 --> 01:01:41.280
And he was full face, chunky-looking in my opinion, a thick dude, massive structure of a guy.

01:01:55.040 --> 01:01:55.235
And this was not George, mine.

01:01:55.235 --> 01:01:57.699
This was one, and he had a robe on.

01:01:57.699 --> 01:01:58.900
He was gorgeous.

01:02:22.960 --> 01:02:23.316
And he grabbed a hold of the back of my truck and he started pushing me and my family in that truck, and we started going.

01:02:23.316 --> 01:02:25.455
Diana goes, 'Oh God, oh!

01:02:25.455 --> 01:02:28.880
' And the kids...

01:02:28.880 --> 01:02:33.622
we were freaking out.

01:02:52.937 --> 01:02:53.474
I grabbed a hold of the steering wheel, but...

01:02:57.653 --> 01:02:58.027
and this is amazing.

01:03:08.607 --> 01:03:08.855
The truck's off.

01:03:08.855 --> 01:03:11.119
This is supernatural.

01:03:11.279 --> 01:03:23.943
I start going on the side of the road, on the shoulder, going faster and faster from a dead stop, all the way up to 70 miles an hour.

01:03:42.880 --> 01:03:43.173
I turn this blinker on to get onto the highway because I'm freaking out at this time, like shock and awe.

01:04:00.319 --> 01:04:00.488
And we start passing people in the left-hand lane going down the road, all the way down for two and a half miles, from Covell all the way there.

01:04:00.488 --> 01:04:02.148
So it's about two and a half miles.

01:04:02.148 --> 01:04:03.383
We go all the way down to...

01:04:03.383 --> 01:04:05.600
there's a gas station at Waterloo.

01:04:06.752 --> 01:04:08.971
I turn right, get off the highway.

01:04:08.971 --> 01:04:10.370
We stop at the stoplight there.

01:04:10.370 --> 01:04:13.920
You'll see it if you want to verify it.

01:04:13.920 --> 01:04:16.011
Go and stop at the stoplight.

01:04:16.011 --> 01:04:21.702
And he pushes us through the stoplight again.

01:04:21.702 --> 01:04:24.052
He starts pushing us again.

01:04:24.052 --> 01:04:26.979
Go through it, go to the gas station.

01:04:26.979 --> 01:04:34.900
And as we get into the gas station, he yanks the back of the tailgate and stops the truck in front of the pump.

01:04:51.440 --> 01:04:52.272
And we just started screaming and he disappeared.

01:04:52.272 --> 01:04:56.651
We just started screaming, 'Glory to God!

01:04:56.651 --> 01:04:57.954
Glory to God!

01:04:57.954 --> 01:05:05.309
' But our windows were down because it was hot, and everybody at their pumps were looking at us, going, 'What's going on?

01:05:05.309 --> 01:05:09.559
' because they could hear us screaming and rejoicing.

01:05:22.453 --> 01:05:22.666
And the other people at the pumps...

01:05:22.880 --> 01:05:23.520
I didn't care.

01:05:24.675 --> 01:05:30.079
I was just freaking out, and the people were looking at us like, 'What is wrong with these people?

01:05:30.079 --> 01:05:32.460
' because they were hearing my kids.

01:05:32.460 --> 01:05:42.549
Megan was yelling already because she was yelling because we were yelling, because Megan's overcoming, but Braden was laughing, we were all screaming, and everybody was cheering and yelling.

01:05:56.433 --> 01:05:57.028
And it was glorious as God took care of us in that moment, and it was just one of those moments that...

01:05:59.406 --> 01:06:05.390
it was shock and awe when God comes through and takes care of you.

01:06:05.390 --> 01:06:16.853
Something you don't earn and something you don't deserve.

01:06:16.853 --> 01:06:20.023
It's just the grace of God.

01:06:20.023 --> 01:06:22.062
It's just the grace of God.

01:06:22.062 --> 01:06:26.928
And it was one of those moments that impacted, I believe, Braden.

01:06:26.928 --> 01:06:28.272
Oh yeah.

01:06:39.159 --> 01:06:39.499
You tell him.

01:06:39.499 --> 01:06:40.079
Yeah.

01:06:40.079 --> 01:06:48.980
'Well, yeah, I looked and you're lifting your foot up off the pedal, off the gas, because you weren't even pushing on the gas at all.

01:07:07.386 --> 01:07:08.212
The whole car was off.

01:07:08.212 --> 01:07:12.079
' It was a...

01:07:12.079 --> 01:07:18.182
yeah, I'll never forget it.

01:07:18.182 --> 01:07:19.639
I'll never forget it.

01:07:27.459 --> 01:07:27.629
And to have power steering...

01:07:55.500 --> 01:07:56.010
I'm not a mechanic, but I was able to get on the highway and everything, and the truck was off.

01:07:56.010 --> 01:07:59.760
And I still don't understand how it all happened.

01:07:59.760 --> 01:08:01.900
My mind can't wrap around it still.

01:08:01.900 --> 01:08:18.362
How did that happen?

01:08:18.362 --> 01:08:45.937
How did you go down the highway with a truck going in supernatural?

01:08:45.937 --> 01:08:47.822
How do you do that?

01:08:47.822 --> 01:08:50.399
How does something like that happen?

01:09:03.499 --> 01:09:03.869
And most people say, 'Well, that's a made-up story.

01:09:03.869 --> 01:09:05.610
' No, it is real.

01:09:05.610 --> 01:09:07.759
It really happened.

01:09:07.759 --> 01:09:26.766
It's one of those ones that I want to watch back when I get to heaven.

01:09:26.766 --> 01:09:51.760
If there's a replay reel of what your life was and everything, I want to rewind it and just say, "I remember when you did that for me.

01:09:51.760 --> 01:09:57.291
I remember when you did that for me.

01:09:57.291 --> 01:10:01.653
" Those are—that's one of those stacking rocks.

01:10:25.291 --> 01:10:30.033
You know how the children of Israel had a stacking rock experience, and every time they wanted to make a monument, like a memorial or whatever, for what God did for them at that point in time, they stacked rocks.

01:10:32.159 --> 01:11:07.440
And I had our stacking rock experience at that moment when God came through for me, and it's one of those moments that I'll never forget.

01:11:07.440 --> 01:11:25.669
Similar to whenever I stepped on the dog and killed that dog by accident—it belonged to my little girl—and God brought it back to life.

01:11:40.823 --> 01:11:41.211
I stepped on that dog and crushed it.

01:11:41.211 --> 01:11:45.079
Guts popped all out the side.

01:11:45.079 --> 01:11:51.291
Blood squirted out of his nose, and we put it outside because the ground was frozen.

01:11:51.291 --> 01:11:52.159
It was snowing.

01:12:06.490 --> 01:12:06.780
I got it for Christmas.

01:12:06.780 --> 01:12:14.754
We were dog breeders, we had puppies, and that was our brand-new dog.

01:12:19.760 --> 01:12:35.051
And we were getting this dog for Paisley for her Christmas, and I stepped on the dog and squashed it to death, to make a long story short.

01:12:35.051 --> 01:12:52.159
And my little girl said, "Are you not going to pray for that dog to get up from the dead, Daddy?

01:12:52.159 --> 01:12:53.706
" And I had lost it.

01:13:27.810 --> 01:13:33.795
I cussed.

01:16:15.120 --> 01:16:15.560
I acted a fool.

01:16:17.320 --> 01:16:23.600
I used so many bad words that night that I probably made a sailor turn red.

01:16:23.600 --> 01:16:27.840
I'm just being real with you.

01:16:40.346 --> 01:16:40.893
I acted a fool.

01:16:40.893 --> 01:16:47.947
And at that moment, I was broken because I was yelling at everybody.

01:16:47.947 --> 01:17:10.829
I was yelling because I killed this dog.

01:17:10.829 --> 01:17:13.510
I freaked out.

01:17:13.510 --> 01:17:22.110
I lost it.

01:17:22.110 --> 01:17:49.371
I was embarrassed by my actions.

01:20:31.246 --> 01:20:31.554
So, my little girl came back to say, "Daddy, will you pray for that dog to get up from the dead?

01:20:31.554 --> 01:20:56.880
" And I said, "Honey, God ain't going to hear me right now for how I just acted.

01:20:56.880 --> 01:21:02.560
God would never listen to me, hon.

01:21:02.560 --> 01:21:11.555
" I said, "My faith is not there.

01:21:11.555 --> 01:21:18.550
I'm embarrassed.

01:21:18.560 --> 01:21:34.381
" She said, "Daddy, all things are possible to him who believes.

01:21:34.381 --> 01:21:38.159
Daddy, all things are possible to him who believes.

01:21:39.600 --> 01:21:58.956
" I said, "Well, Paisley, then you use your faith because Daddy's isn't there.

01:21:58.956 --> 01:22:44.354
" So, she ran up and down the hall just praying as loud as she could in tongues, praying in the spirit, "Oh God, bring my dog back.

01:23:08.860 --> 01:23:09.160
" I've never been challenged like that before in my life.

01:23:10.960 --> 01:23:25.610
I sat in the back of the room with the door closed, just feeling sorry for myself because I just squashed her dog to death and acted a fool, embarrassed by my actions on Christmas.

01:23:25.610 --> 01:23:43.856
I told my wife, "Put that dog in a shoe box, and I'll bury it tomorrow, but just set it out there next to the trash.

01:23:43.856 --> 01:24:00.752
Put it on top, because the can was full of boxes already because of Christmas packages and stuff.

01:24:00.752 --> 01:24:03.520
" So, she put the box up on top.

01:24:03.520 --> 01:24:04.560
She did.

01:24:05.600 --> 01:24:08.800
And it was cold, and it had snowed outside.

01:24:08.800 --> 01:24:19.600
It was probably about 3 inches of snow on the ground, or whatever it was, and it was frozen.

01:24:19.600 --> 01:24:36.827
It was really cold, and I thought, "Man, I'm going to go out there in the snow and dig a place, but I'll do it tomorrow.

01:24:36.827 --> 01:25:04.827
" So, she put that dog in the shoe box because my kids got some shoes for Christmas, and she put that out there and she was going and gathering up the rest of the gift-package trash and stuff around the house.

01:25:04.827 --> 01:25:17.660
And she went out to go put the rest of the trash outside in the can, and when she did, the dog was gone.

01:25:17.660 --> 01:25:22.114
She came back and said, "Brandon, that puppy's gone.

01:25:22.114 --> 01:26:05.740
" Because we had a lot of neighborhood cats and we had raccoons and things, I had thought that maybe one of those varmints or whatever took that dead puppy and got rid of it, you know, like trying to eat it or whatever.

01:26:05.740 --> 01:26:08.848
Sorry, just being real.

01:26:11.720 --> 01:26:28.800
And she went back out there and was looking around, and she heard this squeaking in the bottom of the can.

01:27:13.117 --> 01:27:14.953
And she looked down there, and that dog was on both its back feet trying to get out of that can, and it was alive.

01:27:14.953 --> 01:27:31.394
All restored, with no blood on it at all, completely healed and touched by the power of God.

01:27:31.394 --> 01:27:39.495
She grabbed ahold of that little dog and brought it inside.

01:27:42.605 --> 01:27:44.046
And my little girl started screaming, "I told you, Daddy!

01:28:00.000 --> 01:28:00.251
All things are possible to him who believes.

01:28:01.257 --> 01:28:01.509
I told you, Daddy.

01:28:12.484 --> 01:28:13.573
I told you.

01:28:13.573 --> 01:28:17.307
" And I said, "Oh, God.

01:28:17.307 --> 01:28:46.594
" My wife got that towel and wrapped that dog up and blow-dried that dog and got it hot because it was cold.

01:28:46.594 --> 01:28:49.429
And I held that dog in my hand.

01:28:49.429 --> 01:28:52.440
I held that dog in my arm.

01:29:17.760 --> 01:29:18.227
And I sat there, and I said, "Baby, I'm so sorry.

01:29:40.400 --> 01:29:42.358
" I repented.

01:29:42.358 --> 01:29:57.320
But at that moment, the Lord spoke to me and said, "Brandon, even on your best day, your righteousness is as filthy rags to me.

01:29:57.320 --> 01:30:01.320
Your righteousness is as filthy rags to me.

01:30:01.320 --> 01:30:35.760
In the natural, you are never going to be good enough to do what you think you should do.

01:30:35.760 --> 01:30:39.280
Only by His blood and by His grace are you ever.

01:30:39.280 --> 01:30:42.719
Do you understand?

01:30:42.719 --> 01:30:44.159
Self-righteousness is as filthy rags.

01:30:44.159 --> 01:30:48.446
Self-righteousness is as filthy rags.

01:30:48.446 --> 01:30:49.360
" It checked me.

01:30:49.360 --> 01:30:58.782
But it had nothing to do with me; it was a little girl's faith.

01:30:58.782 --> 01:31:03.280
But He was looking at my heart.

01:31:23.400 --> 01:31:23.729
And what I was saying is like trying to add everything up, and you think because you fast and you pray and you don't have this flesh out that you're qualified.

01:31:23.729 --> 01:31:29.504
"Well, I'm qualified today because I haven't said any bad words.

01:31:29.504 --> 01:31:32.658
I haven't thought any bad thoughts.

01:31:32.658 --> 01:31:39.910
I haven't done anything wrong in the natural.

01:31:39.920 --> 01:31:41.040
Right?

01:31:41.040 --> 01:31:53.370
So, that qualifies me to raise the dead.

01:31:53.370 --> 01:31:57.856
" But your righteousness, even on your best day, is as filthy rags.

01:31:57.856 --> 01:32:03.417
It's all by the grace of God, any day of the week.

01:32:03.417 --> 01:32:05.239
Do you understand?

01:32:52.720 --> 01:32:52.920
Even on your best day.

01:32:56.035 --> 01:33:04.720
And that's what He was trying to show me that day: no matter how much you freaked out, you're still not good enough, even if you hadn't.

01:33:04.720 --> 01:33:10.147
Faith of a mustard seed will move a mountain.

01:33:10.147 --> 01:33:17.920
Faith of a mustard seed will move a mountain.

01:33:17.920 --> 01:33:20.983
Childlike faith.

01:33:30.320 --> 01:33:30.663
The heart of a child.

01:33:54.080 --> 01:33:55.532
And I saw the heart of a child that had no guile, no doubt.

01:33:55.532 --> 01:34:15.191
Even when she saw her daddy yelling and all these things, she said, "Daddy, will you just believe?

01:34:15.191 --> 01:34:17.711
Will you just believe?

01:34:24.959 --> 01:34:25.199
All things are possible to him who believes, Daddy.

01:34:25.199 --> 01:34:40.653
" And it challenged me that night because I saw the grace of God—something you can't earn and something you don't deserve—come through that day.

01:34:40.653 --> 01:34:42.853
You understand?

01:34:42.853 --> 01:35:01.671
God is a good God, and the devil's a bad devil.

01:35:01.671 --> 01:35:10.980
And I thought, you know, a lot of times you think, "Well, it's because I've fasted today.

01:35:10.980 --> 01:35:12.859
Well, I read an extra book today.

01:35:12.859 --> 01:35:17.744
Well, I spent more time today in tongues, so that qualifies me.

01:35:17.744 --> 01:35:26.149
" So, have you ever heard that one before?

01:35:26.159 --> 01:35:37.830
What the Lord did for us?

01:35:37.840 --> 01:35:44.256
Forty percent have it.

01:35:44.256 --> 01:35:48.297
Sixty percent have on that one.

01:36:23.460 --> 01:36:23.800
It blessed my little girl.

01:36:23.800 --> 01:36:26.549
One day, I'll let her on here.

01:36:26.549 --> 01:36:28.320
She's still too young.

01:36:28.320 --> 01:36:32.728
I don't want her on the internet.

01:36:32.728 --> 01:36:35.1000
There's too many weirdos on here.

01:36:35.1000 --> 01:36:38.629
I protect my Paisley.

01:36:38.629 --> 01:36:54.120
There are a lot of strange people.

01:37:03.760 --> 01:37:11.450
And I have to say this because the Holy Spirit said I needed to correct this real quick.

01:37:16.731 --> 01:37:17.234
I'm not picking at these people.

01:37:17.234 --> 01:37:18.582
I don't know them.

01:37:19.268 --> 01:37:19.953
I'm not picking.

01:37:21.069 --> 01:37:24.624
The Lord said, "I hope I don't come across gruff.

01:37:28.239 --> 01:37:30.845
I'm trying to tell you about other people.

01:37:30.845 --> 01:37:33.840
I don't know these people.

01:37:33.840 --> 01:37:44.160
" If Sister Billy knew them, but I'm trying to tell you, I get books every single day in the mail.

01:37:44.160 --> 01:37:48.639
On average, how many do you think on average, Braden?

01:37:48.639 --> 01:37:49.600
Five.

01:37:49.600 --> 01:37:51.422
Five at least.

01:38:06.880 --> 01:38:07.143
I'm not trying to exaggerate.

01:38:07.143 --> 01:38:12.976
So, I'm just trying to be real with you.

01:38:12.976 --> 01:38:15.010
On average, five books a day.

01:38:15.010 --> 01:38:27.859
Five books a day from somebody trying to get me to sponsor their book so that they can make money.

01:38:27.859 --> 01:38:31.119
That's a five.

01:38:37.051 --> 01:38:37.462
It's average on a big day—over ten.

01:38:51.386 --> 01:38:52.133
And I have bookshelves full.

01:39:18.800 --> 01:39:19.060
I didn't realize how many people would do that.

01:39:46.571 --> 01:39:46.857
And I'm telling you, big ones, huge authors, big people, wanting you to read their stuff and promote it on your channel.

01:39:52.355 --> 01:39:52.523
And so, but this was what I asked for.

01:39:52.523 --> 01:39:59.564
But I made that a point to tell people because Diana said, "You make it clear because we get bombarded with it.

01:39:59.564 --> 01:40:01.413
" We get bombarded by it.

01:40:09.131 --> 01:40:09.463
